  "text": "The current study had two aims. First, to test whether two commonly used approaches to dealing with missing data introduce bias in estimates of effectiveness derived in the presence of differential nonadherence between treatment arms. Second, to use data from the GENetic and clinical Predictors Of treatment response in Depression (GENPOD) trial (Lewis et al. 2011; [CITATION_1] to illustrate how to adjust for differential non-adherence in an RCT of two active interventions and hence to derive an unbiased estimate of the efficacy of reboxetine compared with citalopram in the treatment of primary care patients with a new episode of depression.",
